{
  "texts": [
    "We also found that most argument type errors can be fixed by converting the arguments to the correct parameter types.",
    "Argument Hallucination: Upon examining the unified dataset from public sources, we discovered that tool calls frequently include argument values not present in the user query or prior steps.",
    "This issue arises because much of this data is generated by LLMs, which are prone to hallucination, a common problem in LLM-generated content.",
    "We identified two types of hallucination: 1) the generated tool names or argument names do not appear in the provided tool and argument list; and 2) the argument values do not align with the user query or observations from previous steps.",
    "The first type of hallucination is straightforward to address by searching the generated tool call and argument names and matching them with the provided tool list, as they are all structured in JSON, making this process efficient."
  ]
}